  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A linear map is a function between vector spaces that respects the vector space structure — it preserves both addition and scalar multiplication. If you add two vectors and then apply the map, you get the same result as applying the map to each vector separately and then adding. If you scale a vector and then apply the map, you get the same result as applying the map first and then scaling.\n",
